      m
   ), ФPSII, chlorophyl a (C
      a
   ), chlorophyl b (C
      b
   ) and carotenoid (C
      x+c
   ) contents were also higher in NCQD treated plants exposed to UV (A, B and C) as compared to the control group. However, UV light harvesting ability was greater under UV-A and UV-B exposure as compared to UV-C owing to the harvesting ability of NCQD falls under UV-A and UV-B wavelength ranges. The MTT assay demonstrated that the NCQD cytotoxicity towards HeLa cells was also negligible. This novel study proved that bioderived non-toxic fluorescent NCQDs, by supplementing light harvesting capacity of chlorophyll (in vivo), enhanced the efficiency of the photosystem, improved the electron transport chain, upregulated the expression of genes related to CO2 fixation and carbon assimilation, and improved the machinery responsible for photosynthesis in maize.

